♪

00:43.434 --> 00:45.436
♪

01:12.724 --> 01:14.857
♪

01:30.438 --> 01:32.440
♪

02:31.412 --> 02:33.109
Good to get out?

02:33.153 --> 02:35.503
That crisp Chicago air.

02:35.546 --> 02:37.722
A mix of car
exhaust and fish.

02:37.766 --> 02:39.289
Nothing quite like it.

02:39.333 --> 02:41.073
You grew up near here,
didn't you, Solomon?

02:41.117 --> 02:42.466
Humboldt Park.

02:42.510 --> 02:43.772
Two blocks from Saul Bellow.

02:43.815 --> 02:45.295
Those were the days
of great men.

02:45.339 --> 02:46.818
Mr. Waltzer.

02:46.862 --> 02:48.211
Good day to be
out and about.

02:48.255 --> 02:49.604
It is.

02:49.647 --> 02:51.475
We should arrange
a conference for after.

02:51.519 --> 02:53.782
Why is that?After our
next witness,

02:53.825 --> 02:55.740
you'll want to settle.

02:55.784 --> 02:58.613
The man that once did
sell the lion's skin

02:58.656 --> 03:02.791
while the beast lived, was
killed with hunting him.

03:17.109 --> 03:19.851
In all, 28 shots were fired.

03:19.895 --> 03:23.072
Eight came from
the Heckler & Koch P30...

03:24.291 --> 03:25.901
...that was found in the hands

03:25.944 --> 03:28.425
of the deceased, Antonio Phelps.

03:29.687 --> 03:31.820
And he was selling
illegal guns at this site?

03:31.863 --> 03:33.213
Yes. This was an undercover
sting operation

03:33.256 --> 03:34.779
to stop the spread
of illegal arms.

03:35.911 --> 03:37.565
And the remaining 20 shots?

03:37.608 --> 03:39.393
They came from
the two Glock 17s carried

03:39.436 --> 03:40.611
by the arriving officers,

03:40.655 --> 03:43.614
there and there.

03:43.658 --> 03:47.183
And was one of the arriving
officers the defendant,

03:47.227 --> 03:48.576
Detective Daniel
Whitehead?

03:49.751 --> 03:51.318
Your Honor.

03:51.361 --> 03:52.971
Yes, Mr. Waltzer

03:53.015 --> 03:56.453
Not an objection,
so much as a clarification.

03:56.497 --> 04:00.805
Detective Whitehead
is oneof the defendants.

04:00.849 --> 04:03.852
The other is
the Chicago Police Department.

04:05.506 --> 04:07.290
That is correct.

04:07.334 --> 04:09.379
Thank you, Mr. Waltzer.
You may continue.

04:09.423 --> 04:14.863
Now let's turn to the actions
of our client, Rashid Clarkson.

04:15.864 --> 04:17.692
Rashid was here undercover.

04:17.735 --> 04:18.693
Yes.

04:18.736 --> 04:21.348
At this marker here.

04:21.391 --> 04:24.786
And isn't it true, Mr. McVeigh,
that Rashid was unarmed?

04:24.829 --> 04:26.831
Yes. According
to the police report.

04:26.875 --> 04:28.703
Why isn't he objecting?

04:28.746 --> 04:30.705
I don't know.

04:30.748 --> 04:35.840
Whenever I've met a legend,
I have been unimpressed.

04:35.884 --> 04:37.842
Was our client injured

04:37.886 --> 04:39.279
in the crossfire?No.

04:39.322 --> 04:40.976
Where was he injured?

04:41.019 --> 04:42.891
The undercover officer,
Rashid Clarkson, was hit here,

04:42.934 --> 04:44.327
during a foot chase.

04:44.371 --> 04:46.286
He was trying to catch
the other suspect.

04:46.329 --> 04:49.550
Yes.Were you able to determine
the gun that was fired

04:49.593 --> 04:51.595
Yes.

04:51.639 --> 04:54.076
It was the Glock 17 carried
by Detective Whitehead.

04:54.119 --> 04:55.773
Were you able to
determine the trajectory

04:55.817 --> 04:57.993
of the rounds that Detective
Whitehead fired at our client?

04:58.036 --> 05:00.387
Factoring in
Detective Whitehead's height,

05:00.430 --> 05:02.911
and the point of aim
to point of impact,

05:02.954 --> 05:07.394
the trajectory was a downward
angle of 15.6 degrees.

05:07.437 --> 05:08.743
Indicating what?

05:08.786 --> 05:11.093
Officer
Rashid Clarkson was

05:11.136 --> 05:13.791
lying prone on the ground
when he was shot.

05:13.835 --> 05:16.228
And so, our client

05:16.272 --> 05:17.447
will never be able
to walk again...

05:17.491 --> 05:18.709
I think
I'll object to that,

05:18.753 --> 05:20.320
And I
will sustain it.

05:20.363 --> 05:22.017
One more question,
Mr. McVeigh,

05:22.060 --> 05:24.498
before the defense
asks you the same thing.

05:24.541 --> 05:28.415
Are you related to anyone
on our plaintiff's legal team?

05:28.458 --> 05:31.287
Yes. I'm married
to Diane Lockhart,

05:31.331 --> 05:32.506
one of your attorneys.

05:32.549 --> 05:34.595
And has this
biased you in any way?

05:34.638 --> 05:36.423
No.
In fact,

05:36.466 --> 05:40.165
have you ever testified on the
other side from Ms. Lockhart?

05:40.209 --> 05:41.558
Yes, on three cases.

05:41.602 --> 05:42.864
Well, that can't
go ever well at home.

05:44.692 --> 05:46.824
Well, we understand that
facts always eclipse emotion.

05:46.868 --> 05:48.826
Thank you, Mr. McVeigh.

05:48.870 --> 05:50.785
Mr. Waltzer, anything?

05:50.828 --> 05:52.613
Yes.

05:52.656 --> 05:55.137
Mr. McVeigh,
have you ever been charged

05:55.180 --> 05:57.269
with perjury in any case?

05:59.489 --> 06:00.882
No, sir.

06:00.925 --> 06:03.537
Okay. Thank you.

06:12.850 --> 06:14.765
Hey, you were great.

06:14.809 --> 06:16.724
Thank you.

06:16.767 --> 06:18.682
I don't think
I should kiss you here.

06:18.726 --> 06:20.162
How about later?

06:20.205 --> 06:21.772
30.

06:21.816 --> 06:24.384
I'll leave the door unlocked.

06:24.427 --> 06:28.257
Hey, uh, you have never been
charged with perjury, right?

06:28.300 --> 06:29.650
Right.

06:31.347 --> 06:33.958
That was a weird cross.
Maybe he's going senile.

06:35.525 --> 06:36.744
Mr. Waltzer.

06:36.787 --> 06:38.398
Why don't you ride with us?

06:38.441 --> 06:40.400
Oh, I'd like that.

06:43.359 --> 06:45.840
8.3 million.

06:45.883 --> 06:47.711
I think we could
accept that.

06:47.755 --> 06:50.279
I was hoping for more, but
I'm feeling sorry for you.

06:50.322 --> 06:51.933
We have a
sympathetic client,

06:51.976 --> 06:56.372
Mr. Waltzer, in a wheelchair,
shot by a racist cop.

06:56.416 --> 06:57.982
If this goes to verdict,

06:58.026 --> 07:00.681
the CPD could end up
paying more than 12 million.

07:00.724 --> 07:03.553
We're offering you a deal.
8.3 now, and we're done.

07:03.597 --> 07:05.468
Thank you, but
I'm enjoying court.

07:05.512 --> 07:07.862
I used to work at a
car wash right there.

07:07.905 --> 07:09.429
$1.25 an hour.

07:09.472 --> 07:13.171
Mr. Waltzer, you do realize
you're losing?

07:13.215 --> 07:16.218
That's what Justice Scalia
said to me in 1991.

07:16.261 --> 07:18.568
One of my strengths is
never knowing I'm losing.

07:22.485 --> 07:25.880
All I ever wanted
was to be a cop.

07:25.923 --> 07:27.708
I'm born and raised
in this city.

07:27.751 --> 07:30.450
I love it.
I wanted to give back.

07:32.495 --> 07:34.454
That was taken from me.

07:34.497 --> 07:36.891
See, I'm 34.

07:36.934 --> 07:38.849
It's not how I expected
my life to go.

07:40.416 --> 07:42.636
Sorry.

07:42.679 --> 07:45.595
Now I can't even
walk my dog.

07:45.639 --> 07:47.118
My wife has to turn
me over in bed.

07:47.162 --> 07:48.816
He's not objecting to anything.

07:48.859 --> 07:50.731
I think you can push this.

07:50.774 --> 07:53.647
Officer Clarkson,
were you familiar

07:53.690 --> 07:57.781
with Detective Whitehead
prior to the shooting?

07:57.825 --> 07:59.479
No.

07:59.522 --> 08:01.350
So why do you think he shot you?

08:01.393 --> 08:03.221
He saw a black face
and decided to shoot.

08:03.265 --> 08:05.136
I was screaming at him

08:05.180 --> 08:08.836
that I was unarmed, that
I was an undercover cop.

08:08.879 --> 08:10.925
I was trying to chase down
one of the suspects.

08:10.968 --> 08:12.230
Had you heard rumors of

08:12.274 --> 08:14.363
Detective Whitehead's racism
before?

08:14.406 --> 08:15.756
Uh, one-one second.

08:15.799 --> 08:20.456
Uh, Mr. Waltzer, uh,
do you want to object to that?

08:20.500 --> 08:23.285
No, thank you, Your Honor.

08:23.328 --> 08:26.114
I trust the jury
to discern what is fact

08:26.157 --> 08:28.377
and what is opinion.

08:30.161 --> 08:32.294
Okay.I heard stories about Whitehead

08:32.337 --> 08:34.078
using drop guns

08:34.122 --> 08:38.126
and going out of his way
to harass black arrestees.

08:38.169 --> 08:40.302
I was told to
watch out for him.

08:40.345 --> 08:41.564
Thank you, Officer.

08:41.608 --> 08:43.044
Uh, Mr. Waltzer?

08:43.087 --> 08:44.785
Yes.

08:51.705 --> 08:52.749
Hello.

08:52.793 --> 08:54.490
Hi.

08:54.534 --> 08:57.711
You mentioned not being able
to walk your dog earlier.

08:57.754 --> 09:00.670
What kind of dog?

09:00.714 --> 09:04.369
A bull terrier. Augustus.

09:04.413 --> 09:06.241
Augustus.

09:06.284 --> 09:09.549
I-- my guess is he wasn't named
after the first Roman emperor.

09:09.592 --> 09:11.768
No, a friend.SOLOMON: I see.

09:11.812 --> 09:13.596
And you still have Augustus?

09:13.640 --> 09:15.598
Your Honor, objection.
Relevance.

09:15.642 --> 09:17.905
Your Honor, I didn't bring up
the dog, the witness did.

09:17.948 --> 09:19.602
I'm just getting
a fuller picture.Okay.

09:19.646 --> 09:22.213
I have no idea
where this is going,

09:22.257 --> 09:24.128
but overruled.

09:24.172 --> 09:26.304
So do you still have Augustus?

09:26.348 --> 09:29.394
No. He died a few months back.

09:29.438 --> 09:30.657
I see.

09:30.700 --> 09:32.180
And what did he die of?

09:32.223 --> 09:34.356
It was
natural causes.

09:34.399 --> 09:35.575
He got old.

09:35.618 --> 09:36.706
Big dogs have
a harder time.

09:36.750 --> 09:38.099
So are you saying
he died naturally?

09:38.142 --> 09:41.493
Or do you mean he was put down?

09:41.537 --> 09:43.887
Uh, he was put down.
I see.

09:43.931 --> 09:45.497
And a veterinarian did this?

09:45.541 --> 09:47.543
Yes.And it wasn't
done illegally,

09:47.587 --> 09:49.806
after an injury
from a dog fight?

09:49.850 --> 09:51.416
Objection, Your Honor.

09:51.460 --> 09:53.331
Relevance. Not in evidence.

09:53.375 --> 09:55.029
I think the relevance
will become clear, Your Honor.

09:55.072 --> 09:57.031
Um, get to the point,

09:57.074 --> 09:58.859
Mr. Waltzer.

09:58.902 --> 10:02.863
Officer Clarkson,
in June of 2014,

10:02.906 --> 10:04.473
didn't Internal Affairs

10:04.516 --> 10:08.477
investigate reports that
you were conducting dog fights

10:08.520 --> 10:10.044
Objection, Your Honor.after complaints

10:10.087 --> 10:11.741
by Jean Bibb, a neighbor?Objection.

10:11.785 --> 10:13.047
Objection!

10:13.090 --> 10:14.657
Your Honor,

10:14.701 --> 10:15.832
this line of questioning
is meant purely

10:15.876 --> 10:17.138
to disparage our client.

10:17.181 --> 10:18.443
There is no evidence
of this, Your Honor.

10:18.487 --> 10:19.749
And even if there were,

10:19.793 --> 10:21.359
it would have no connection
to this shooting.

10:21.403 --> 10:23.361
Sorry, Your Honor,
if I could speak?

10:23.405 --> 10:25.276
I'm not used to
this new way of debate

10:25.320 --> 10:26.713
where the loudest voice wins.

10:26.756 --> 10:28.366
Go ahead.

10:28.410 --> 10:29.933
I think any Internal Affairs
investigation

10:29.977 --> 10:31.805
has a direct bearing
on this case.

10:31.848 --> 10:33.023
That is not true.

10:33.067 --> 10:34.416
Mr. Boseman. Shh.

10:34.459 --> 10:36.592
Where is the evidence
of this investigation?

10:36.636 --> 10:38.376
My paralegal found
an article referring

10:38.420 --> 10:40.291
to a leaked I.A. report.

10:40.335 --> 10:41.989
I'm subpoenaing the department

10:42.032 --> 10:44.165
even as we speak.Okay. I want evidence

10:44.208 --> 10:45.601
brought to me by tomorrow
morning, and I'll rule

10:45.645 --> 10:46.820
on the admissibility
of this questioning.

10:46.863 --> 10:48.691
The bell has already
been rung, Your Honor.

10:48.735 --> 10:50.084
And if there
is no evidence,

10:50.127 --> 10:52.826
we will unring it;
that is all I can offer.

10:54.262 --> 10:57.091
Come on, man, it's not true.

10:57.134 --> 10:59.702
How didyour dog die?

10:59.746 --> 11:01.356
Exactly as I said.
He was getting old.

11:01.399 --> 11:03.097
Look, I'm not lying.

11:03.140 --> 11:04.359
Could this neighbor,

11:04.402 --> 11:06.361
Mrs. Bibb, have been lying?

11:06.404 --> 11:08.189
I don't even have a neighbor.
We live out in the country.

11:08.232 --> 11:09.930
Okay. Jay,
check if there are

11:09.973 --> 11:11.888
any Internal Affairs reports
we don't know about.

11:11.932 --> 11:13.934
And, Marissa,

11:13.977 --> 11:16.893
you check if there's any news
reporting on this at all.

11:16.937 --> 11:18.939
♪

11:29.427 --> 11:31.168
Who are you visiting?Craig Savador, please.

11:56.193 --> 11:58.761
So, hey.

11:58.805 --> 12:00.763
Hey.

12:05.681 --> 12:08.118
Let's see this.

12:09.250 --> 12:10.555
Dope.

12:10.599 --> 12:11.687
Okay.

12:12.906 --> 12:14.734
This is Basquiat-level dope.

12:14.777 --> 12:16.866
Yeah, I took what you did
and riffed off it a bit.

12:16.910 --> 12:19.434
Oh, so, y-you jocking
my style now, huh?

12:19.477 --> 12:20.652
You wish.

12:20.696 --> 12:22.045
That's classic Boondocks.

12:22.089 --> 12:23.786
I'm just taking it
to another level.

12:23.830 --> 12:26.223
Hey.
Ah.

12:26.267 --> 12:27.659
Now it's your move.

12:33.840 --> 12:36.756
So what up? Talk to me.

12:36.799 --> 12:39.280
It's looking good.

12:39.323 --> 12:41.151
I heard that before.

12:41.195 --> 12:42.762
It's different
this time.

12:42.805 --> 12:45.503
I heard that before, too.

12:45.547 --> 12:48.115
I think some stuff
is about to drop in court

12:48.158 --> 12:49.725
that can help your appeal.

12:49.769 --> 12:51.858
But your firm don't know
anything about me.

12:51.901 --> 12:53.033
No.

12:53.076 --> 12:54.599
That doesn't matter.

12:54.643 --> 12:56.471
There's damning stuff
about Whitehead.

12:56.514 --> 12:58.821
And his use
of drop guns.

13:00.867 --> 13:03.304
Uh... you serious?

13:03.347 --> 13:05.828
Yeah. Call your lawyer.

13:05.872 --> 13:08.004
Tell him to get to court
and use what we're getting

13:08.048 --> 13:09.266
on the record.

13:12.879 --> 13:14.184
Hey.

13:17.666 --> 13:19.842
What do you think?
Oh.

13:19.886 --> 13:22.584
I think Solomon knows
he has a losing case,

13:22.627 --> 13:25.369
and he wants to distract us
as well as the jury.

13:25.413 --> 13:27.763
He doesn't have the facts
on his side.
Right.

13:27.807 --> 13:30.635
So he wants us
chasing our tails.

13:30.679 --> 13:33.682
And here we are,
chasing our tails.

13:33.725 --> 13:35.379
Yeah.
Where you going?

13:35.423 --> 13:37.512
Oh, uh, court.

13:37.555 --> 13:39.122
For what?

13:39.166 --> 13:41.777
Oh, I-I just--
I promised someone.

13:41.821 --> 13:43.170
Who?

13:43.213 --> 13:45.433
Do you mind if
I don't answer that?

13:45.476 --> 13:47.827
It's-it's really--
It's not a big deal.

13:52.092 --> 13:55.617
Thank you... for all, uh,
joining me here today.

13:55.660 --> 13:58.054
I'm, Judge Trig Mullaney,
a new appointee here.

13:58.098 --> 14:00.056
And...

14:00.100 --> 14:01.666
Oh, of course.

14:01.710 --> 14:03.277
Thank you.

14:03.320 --> 14:05.105
Cleanup on aisle seven.

14:06.541 --> 14:08.804
I'm Judge, uh...
I'm Judge Trig Mulla--

14:08.848 --> 14:10.240
I'm Judge Trig Mullaney,

14:10.284 --> 14:12.286
a new appointee here,
in new robes.

14:12.329 --> 14:14.592
Uh, and I will be
your judge today,

14:14.636 --> 14:17.030
and, uh, you will be...

14:17.073 --> 14:19.510
my, um...

14:19.554 --> 14:22.296
What should I call you?
My arrestees.

14:23.993 --> 14:25.038
You made it.

14:25.081 --> 14:26.822
Yeah. I said I would.

14:26.866 --> 14:29.216
I think I'm fucked.
This guy's a Trump appointee.

14:29.259 --> 14:30.913
All right, just
follow my lead,

14:30.957 --> 14:32.436
and don't say
anything radical.

14:32.480 --> 14:34.569
Oh, like we need to
assassinate the president?

14:34.612 --> 14:36.136
No, don't even joke
about that.

14:36.179 --> 14:38.181
Let's just take this
one thing at a time here.

14:38.225 --> 14:40.618
Uh, you, at the...
at the thing there.

14:40.662 --> 14:42.925
The lectern, Your Honor.

14:42.969 --> 14:44.057
The lectern, yes.

14:44.100 --> 14:46.537
You are with...

14:46.581 --> 14:48.017
Who are you with?

14:48.061 --> 14:49.497
The Department of Justice.Of Justice, yes.

14:49.540 --> 14:50.890
AUSA Monica Timmons.

14:50.933 --> 14:52.674
Good. Good.

14:52.717 --> 14:55.285
And, uh, you--
contestant number one.

14:55.329 --> 14:58.158
Come on down.

14:58.201 --> 15:01.291
I am Diane Lockhart,
representing Tully Nelson.

15:01.335 --> 15:03.250
Okay.

15:03.293 --> 15:05.339
Wh-- And what are
the accusations?

15:05.382 --> 15:07.776
The charges, Your Honor?
Mr. Tully's charged with

15:07.819 --> 15:09.647
incitement to riot
and resisting arrest.

15:09.691 --> 15:10.866
Application for release

15:10.910 --> 15:12.259
on the defendant's
own recognizance.

15:12.302 --> 15:14.304
Government opposes.

15:16.654 --> 15:19.483
Okay.

15:21.311 --> 15:23.792
Thank you. That's fine.

15:23.835 --> 15:26.099
Shh. Thank you.

15:26.142 --> 15:28.492
Thanks. I'm gonna need
a moment to think on that.

15:28.536 --> 15:29.929
Um...

15:29.972 --> 15:32.540
ponder it, you know.

15:32.583 --> 15:34.542
Conjugate.

15:34.585 --> 15:36.152
Your Honor,

15:36.196 --> 15:39.764
...bail is customarily set,

15:39.808 --> 15:41.766
even in Class A felonies.

15:41.810 --> 15:44.595
Yeah. Yep, well...

15:44.639 --> 15:48.556
in my court, we do not follow,
you know... customary things.

15:48.599 --> 15:50.297
The court should know
that we will be filing

15:50.340 --> 15:51.733
an interlocutory appeal

15:51.776 --> 15:53.474
on this ruling--

15:53.517 --> 15:56.129
and that's not
a good thing--

15:56.172 --> 15:58.522
unless bail is granted.

15:58.566 --> 16:01.003
Your Honor,

16:01.047 --> 16:02.526
the government
supports detention because

16:02.570 --> 16:04.137
the defendant is a flight risk.

16:04.180 --> 16:05.747
The crime involved

16:05.790 --> 16:07.749
destruction of property.

16:07.792 --> 16:10.012
At a post office.It did, huh?

16:10.056 --> 16:11.622
Without bail, Your Honor,

16:11.666 --> 16:13.842
we will be asking you
to honor the Daubert standard.

16:13.885 --> 16:15.757
Your Honor, the Daubert
standard has nothing to do...

16:15.800 --> 16:16.888
Whether it's res judicata

16:16.932 --> 16:19.152
or stare decisis,
there is no basis

16:19.195 --> 16:20.718
for imposing some

16:20.762 --> 16:24.026
Draconian policy with regard
to bail nunc pro tunc.

16:24.070 --> 16:26.115
Your Honor, the defense is now
just making up words.

16:26.159 --> 16:27.595
Excuse me.
You insult His Honor.

16:27.638 --> 16:29.031
I think he knows
the difference

16:29.075 --> 16:31.251
between a legal standard
and a lawyerly trick.

16:37.126 --> 16:38.998
God, that was intense!
Oh...

16:39.041 --> 16:41.391
Listen, you need to get
a permanent lawyer, Tully.

