Diane, the jury will be looking
at you to see your reaction.

31:05.515 --> 31:08.518
So? I won't react.

31:08.562 --> 31:10.694
Can you not?

31:10.738 --> 31:14.394
I can not.

31:21.967 --> 31:23.969
You sure
you're all right?

31:24.012 --> 31:25.405
Cool as a cucumber.

31:25.448 --> 31:27.233
Your Honor,
we would like to call

31:27.276 --> 31:29.539
our first witness,
but I must apologize.

31:29.583 --> 31:31.759
We've had to replace
our ballistics expert

31:31.802 --> 31:33.543
at the last minute.Objection, Your Honor.

31:33.587 --> 31:34.718
Witness was not disclosed

31:34.762 --> 31:36.024
prior to trial.

31:36.068 --> 31:37.896
Our expert witness
was taken sick.

31:37.939 --> 31:39.593
It's merely a replacement.

31:39.636 --> 31:41.508
I'll allow. Don't worry.

31:41.551 --> 31:43.162
You'll-you'll be given time
to prepare.

31:43.205 --> 31:44.337
Go ahead, Mr. Waltzer.

31:44.380 --> 31:45.816
We call Holly Westfall.

31:50.169 --> 31:51.692
What?

31:51.735 --> 31:55.435
Yup. We're deep
in soap opera territory.

31:58.612 --> 32:02.224
According to the
plaintiff's expert, Mr. McVeigh,

32:02.268 --> 32:04.270
the angle of the bullet

32:04.313 --> 32:06.011
that resulted
in the plaintiff's injury

32:06.054 --> 32:08.622
was 15.6 degrees.

32:08.665 --> 32:10.363
First of all,
do you agree with that?

32:10.406 --> 32:12.147
No, unfortunately.

32:12.191 --> 32:14.758
And do...

32:14.802 --> 32:16.760
Why do you say "unfortunately"?

32:16.804 --> 32:19.459
Well, because I have
deep respect for Mr. McVeigh.

32:19.502 --> 32:21.113
I just think
he's wrong on this.

32:21.156 --> 32:22.679
I see.
So, you-you don't

32:22.723 --> 32:25.291
think Rashid was lying
on the ground

32:25.334 --> 32:27.162
in front of the warehouse
when he was shot?

32:27.206 --> 32:29.469
No. From my analysis,
he was hit

32:29.512 --> 32:32.167
in the crossfire in the
salvage yard warehouse earlier.

32:32.211 --> 32:34.996
I see.
Now, Ms. Westfall,

32:35.040 --> 32:37.042
you know Mr. McVeigh personally,

32:37.085 --> 32:38.478
is that correct?

32:38.521 --> 32:40.045
Kurt McVeigh was
my ballistics professor

32:40.088 --> 32:41.437
at one time.

32:41.481 --> 32:43.135
And did he ever
share with you

32:43.178 --> 32:45.789
his approach
to persuading a jury?

32:45.833 --> 32:48.792
Yes. He believes in taking the
jury to the scene of the crime

32:48.836 --> 32:50.751
because it makes
more of an impression.

32:50.794 --> 32:53.667
It can also bolster your
credibility as an expert

32:53.710 --> 32:56.278
and make it more likely
that you can persuade them.

32:56.322 --> 32:58.585
And did he tell you all this
in the classroom?

32:58.628 --> 33:00.891
No.

33:00.935 --> 33:03.546
I see.
Where did he tell you this?

33:03.590 --> 33:05.244
Objection, Your Honor.
Relevance?

33:05.287 --> 33:06.680
It helps the jury gauge

33:06.723 --> 33:08.116
the value of the statement,
Your Honor.

33:08.160 --> 33:10.031
Overruled.

33:10.075 --> 33:14.427
No, it wasn't in the classroom.

33:14.470 --> 33:16.168
It was in a private setting.

33:16.211 --> 33:18.039
What kind of
a private setting?

33:18.083 --> 33:20.215
Again, objection, Your Honor,
as to relevance.

33:20.259 --> 33:22.652
Ms. Westfall, you've been told
to answer the question.

33:25.916 --> 33:29.920
I had a relationship
with Mr. McVeigh,

33:29.964 --> 33:31.705
and he shared this
with me then.

33:31.748 --> 33:33.098
In bed?

33:33.141 --> 33:34.708
Your Honor,
I would really prefer

33:34.751 --> 33:36.797
It goes
to Ms. Westfall's

33:36.840 --> 33:38.364
knowledge of Mr. McVeigh.

33:38.407 --> 33:41.758
You are, uh...

33:41.802 --> 33:44.370
you're under oath, Ms. Westfall.

33:48.591 --> 33:50.898
Yes, I believe it was in bed.

33:50.941 --> 33:52.943
You believe that
Mr. McVeigh still has these

33:52.987 --> 33:55.859
same beliefs and concerns,
though, isn't that right?

33:55.903 --> 33:57.122
Yes.

33:57.165 --> 33:58.775
And why is that?

33:58.819 --> 34:02.344
Uh, because we've discussed
cases since then.

34:02.388 --> 34:05.304
At ballistics conferences?

34:05.347 --> 34:06.740
No.

34:06.783 --> 34:08.350
Where then?

34:08.394 --> 34:12.093
We still socialize.
We get drinks sometimes.

34:12.137 --> 34:14.791
And you have no reason
to believe that Mr. McVeigh

34:14.835 --> 34:18.143
would not tell you what he was
thinking and feeling?

34:18.186 --> 34:21.146
I've never known him
to lie to me.

34:25.759 --> 34:28.066
So, what can you tell us?

34:30.764 --> 34:32.461
Nothing.

34:32.505 --> 34:35.247
Holly Westfall's really
damaged your credibility.

34:35.290 --> 34:36.683
We need to damage hers.

34:36.726 --> 34:38.163
I understand that.

34:38.206 --> 34:40.252
I'll offer testimony
on ballistics.

34:40.295 --> 34:42.036
That's what I do.

34:42.080 --> 34:44.517
Nothing personal.

34:44.560 --> 34:46.345
Your relationship

34:46.388 --> 34:49.348
with Ms. Westfall
can ruin this whole case.

34:49.391 --> 34:51.001
That is personal.

34:51.045 --> 34:54.614
Could you give us a minute?

35:06.800 --> 35:08.932
I need your help
on this.

35:08.976 --> 35:11.370
The jury was
convinced by her.

35:11.413 --> 35:13.546
I know.

35:16.592 --> 35:20.292
We need something about her
from your perspective.

35:20.335 --> 35:21.597
I can't do that.

35:21.641 --> 35:22.772
Well, she did it.

35:22.816 --> 35:26.167
Doesn't matter.

35:26.211 --> 35:29.736
So, you're loyal...

35:29.779 --> 35:31.216
to her?

35:31.259 --> 35:32.391
I wouldn't put it that way.

35:32.434 --> 35:34.219
No

35:34.262 --> 35:38.092
Not to my firm,
not to my client...

35:38.136 --> 35:39.485
not to me.

35:39.528 --> 35:41.313
Hold on.You don't kiss and tell?

35:41.356 --> 35:42.749
Is that it?

35:42.792 --> 35:44.620
That would be disloyal?Diane.

35:44.664 --> 35:46.709
Don't you fucking
come any closer to me!

35:46.753 --> 35:47.884
I had a drink with her.Not another word.

35:47.928 --> 35:48.885
Just hear me out.
No.

35:48.929 --> 35:50.322
I will not be that wife.

35:50.365 --> 35:51.975
Who said that?

35:52.019 --> 35:54.543
I don't want to hear
a story about how she called

35:54.587 --> 35:56.197
or you ran into her...I did.

35:56.241 --> 35:57.633
...or you didn't mention it
because it didn't mean anything.

35:57.677 --> 35:58.808
It didn't.

35:58.852 --> 36:02.334
You lied, Kurt!It wasn't like that.

36:02.377 --> 36:03.813
I'm not that woman.

36:05.728 --> 36:07.730
I will not do this.

36:20.700 --> 36:23.485
Hey. I know you.

36:23.529 --> 36:25.183
The funeral.
Right.

36:25.226 --> 36:27.185
Right. People were
dying on you.

36:27.228 --> 36:30.231
They still are.

36:30.275 --> 36:32.842
Yeah. People disappoint.

36:32.886 --> 36:34.409
What are you drinking?

36:34.453 --> 36:37.325
Oh, um, red wine.

36:37.369 --> 36:39.240
California Cabernet?

36:39.284 --> 36:41.721
Sure. Whatever.

36:41.764 --> 36:43.853
Actually, I asked our partner,

36:43.897 --> 36:46.856
who hired you for,
for that reception,

36:46.900 --> 36:48.162
where she found you.

36:48.206 --> 36:49.424
That's why I'm here.

36:49.468 --> 36:52.122
Because I am
just that charming.

36:54.168 --> 36:56.431
I can pay.

36:56.475 --> 36:59.086
No, I do it for friends.

36:59.129 --> 37:02.045
Hmm. And am I a friend?

37:02.089 --> 37:05.484
♪ And people like me, uh...

37:12.882 --> 37:14.275
Friend's advice?

37:14.319 --> 37:17.060
Don't get addicted?
No.

37:17.104 --> 37:20.542
Find more than one source.

37:36.341 --> 37:38.691
♪

37:50.442 --> 37:52.835
♪

38:07.197 --> 38:09.809
You up?

38:09.852 --> 38:13.160
Actually, yes.

38:13.203 --> 38:16.990
Why the Beretta?

38:17.033 --> 38:19.079
Oh, you know guns?

38:19.122 --> 38:20.515
This is not a gun.
It's a pistol.

38:20.559 --> 38:22.300
And I know it's illegal

38:22.343 --> 38:25.433
to modify the milsurp magazine
for a 92S.

38:25.477 --> 38:29.089
You are a mess
of contradictions.

38:29.132 --> 38:31.526
Why are you carrying?Protection.

38:31.570 --> 38:37.010
I don't like guns, but...
these are dangerous times.

38:39.055 --> 38:41.362
Tell me what you said
in court was a joke.

38:41.406 --> 38:43.538
Why?

38:43.582 --> 38:47.368
You don't believe
in regime change?

38:47.412 --> 38:49.283
You're discussing a crime
with your lawyer.

38:49.327 --> 38:50.371
No, no, no, no.

38:50.415 --> 38:52.199
I am discussing politics.

38:52.242 --> 38:53.809
Violence is not politics.

38:53.853 --> 38:56.377
Oh

39:20.488 --> 39:22.621
This won't slow us down.

39:27.452 --> 39:28.801
Excuse me, Mr. McVeigh?

39:28.844 --> 39:30.585
Maia Rindell.

39:30.629 --> 39:32.065
Oh, yes, Diane's goddaughter.

39:32.108 --> 39:33.588
Hello. How are you?Fine.

39:33.632 --> 39:36.461
Thank you. I was wondering
if I could get your help

39:36.504 --> 39:38.463
with a case
I'm working on.

39:38.506 --> 39:40.769
We think a gun was
planted by a policeman...

39:40.813 --> 39:42.597
Sorry, um, I've got
a lot going on.

39:42.641 --> 39:44.860
I'd better give Diane
her space right now.

39:44.904 --> 39:46.209
She's not involved
with this case.

39:46.253 --> 39:48.298
Well, I can
recommend someone.

39:48.342 --> 39:49.865
The policeman was
Detective Whitehead.

39:49.909 --> 39:53.434
We think he planted
a gun on our client,

39:53.478 --> 39:57.090
turning a three-year
drug sentence into 15.

39:57.133 --> 39:59.745
We just need you
to look at the file.

39:59.788 --> 40:01.050
Mr. McVeigh?

40:01.094 --> 40:03.139
You're next.

40:03.183 --> 40:04.489
Thank you for returning.

40:04.532 --> 40:06.142
You're welcome.

40:06.186 --> 40:09.058
The plaintiff attorneys
have already pointed out that

40:09.102 --> 40:10.538
you and Ms. Lockhart
are married.

40:10.582 --> 40:11.757
Yes.

40:11.800 --> 40:12.975
But, to be exact,

40:13.019 --> 40:16.152
the two of you are separated,
is that right?

40:16.196 --> 40:18.067
Yes.

40:18.111 --> 40:20.940
And have you asked her
to reconcile with you?

40:20.983 --> 40:22.681
Objection. Relevance.

40:22.724 --> 40:24.683
This is rebuttal
testimony, Your Honor.

40:24.726 --> 40:27.468
I never intended to venture
into personal territory,

40:27.512 --> 40:28.904
but the plaintiff attorneys

40:28.948 --> 40:30.819
have opened the door
to this relationship.

40:30.863 --> 40:33.256
That is true. Overruled.

40:33.300 --> 40:36.085
Did you ask Diane Lockhart
to reconcile with you?

40:36.129 --> 40:37.783
Yes.

40:37.826 --> 40:40.220
More than once?Yes.

40:40.263 --> 40:41.830
And why was that?

40:43.876 --> 40:46.487
I don't understand the question.

40:46.531 --> 40:47.967
You injured your wife deeply

40:48.010 --> 40:49.838
and you wanted to make amends,
is that correct?

40:51.840 --> 40:53.842
Yes. I...

40:59.021 --> 41:00.545
I hurt her.

41:00.588 --> 41:02.416
So did you
buy her jewelry?

41:02.460 --> 41:04.505
Come on. Objection,
Your Honor.

41:04.549 --> 41:07.552
This is an
expert witness, Your Honor.

41:07.595 --> 41:08.988
Gifts between lawyers
and witnesses

41:09.031 --> 41:10.468
are always subject
to examination.

41:10.511 --> 41:13.775
Cautiously overruled.

41:13.819 --> 41:15.864
I did not buy her jewelry, no.

41:15.908 --> 41:18.476
Did you take her on a vacation?No.

41:18.519 --> 41:21.261
But you apologized?Yes.

41:21.304 --> 41:23.263
And yet she still
did not reconcile?

41:23.306 --> 41:25.091
Asked and answered, Your Honor.

41:25.134 --> 41:26.919
You injured
your wife deeply,

41:26.962 --> 41:29.225
and you wanted to make amends.
You wanted your wife

41:29.269 --> 41:31.663
to reconcile with you,

41:31.706 --> 41:34.361
but you didn't buy
her perfume or jewelry

41:34.404 --> 41:36.885
or take her
on a vacation.

41:36.929 --> 41:40.062
What you did do was
testify at this trial.

41:40.106 --> 41:41.890
Objection!

41:41.934 --> 41:44.893
Counselor is not only
testifying, Your Honor,

41:44.937 --> 41:47.417
he's also drawing the
most absurd conclusions.

41:47.461 --> 41:49.942
I don't need an answer,
Your Honor.

41:49.985 --> 41:51.421
I think it's obvious.

42:03.564 --> 42:04.739
Could you hold that, please?

42:06.959 --> 42:09.527
Thanks.

42:16.838 --> 42:19.667
Do I know you?

42:19.711 --> 42:23.105
I don't think so.
Huh.

42:23.149 --> 42:26.892
You're a cop, right?
No.

42:26.935 --> 42:30.243
Ah.

42:30.286 --> 42:32.288
You got that cop look.

42:34.377 --> 42:36.728
Hi. Diane Lockhart, please.

42:41.254 --> 42:42.777
Uh, Maia Rindell.

42:48.174 --> 42:51.090
Hey.

42:51.133 --> 42:54.528
It looks good with furniture.

42:54.572 --> 42:57.662
Thanks.
Oof.

42:57.705 --> 42:59.925
A bit chilly.

43:03.450 --> 43:06.714
I've been feeling
a bit adrift these days.

43:06.758 --> 43:10.762
And I'm trying to find
some solid ground again.

43:10.805 --> 43:12.111
Sounds smart.

43:13.765 --> 43:18.247
I think that solid ground
means not being with you.

43:21.033 --> 43:23.339
That was quick.

43:23.383 --> 43:24.819
Did you find something?

43:24.863 --> 43:26.647
Yeah, yeah,
I think so.

43:26.691 --> 43:28.954
This is Lucca.
She's working on it, too.

43:28.997 --> 43:30.956
Yeah, I know Lucca.Hi, Kurt.

43:30.999 --> 43:33.828
This is the serial number
of the Glock 17

43:33.872 --> 43:36.701
that you said was planted
on Craig Savador.

43:36.744 --> 43:38.790
Mm-hmm.
376-

43:38.833 --> 43:41.401
88345.

43:41.444 --> 43:42.924
Okay.

43:42.968 --> 43:45.448
Now, there were no matches
in the police database,

43:45.492 --> 43:46.841
but I found this.

43:46.885 --> 43:49.365
Four Glock 17s recovered
from the robbery

43:49.409 --> 43:51.716
of a sporting goods
store a year earlier.

43:53.761 --> 43:57.199
88343, 88344,

43:57.243 --> 43:59.637
and...88346.

43:59.680 --> 44:01.029
45 is missing.

44:01.073 --> 44:03.075
That's right.So whoever investigated

44:03.118 --> 44:05.251
this sporting goods
robbery took it.

44:05.294 --> 44:06.992
That's my theory.Whitehead.

44:07.035 --> 44:09.342
He wasn't the investigator.

44:09.385 --> 44:11.300
Then who?

44:11.344 --> 44:13.085
Rashid Clarkson.

44:27.360 --> 44:30.145
Uh... what's going on?

44:33.061 --> 44:36.108
I asked you in court
if you knew Officer Whitehead.

44:36.151 --> 44:38.458
You said no.

44:38.501 --> 44:41.809
I hate it
when clients lie to me.

44:41.853 --> 44:43.724
What are you talking about?

44:43.768 --> 44:46.596
I take it personally.
I shouldn't, but I do.

44:46.640 --> 44:48.076
A low-level drug dealer

44:48.120 --> 44:51.166
is doing a decade for possession
of a Glock 17 handgun.

44:51.210 --> 44:53.038
You took it from a
sporting goods robbery,

44:53.081 --> 44:55.736
but you left it off
your evidence report.

44:55.780 --> 44:57.607
The drug dealer said
that the gun wasn't his.

44:57.651 --> 44:58.913
That it was planted

44:58.957 --> 45:02.134
by the arresting officer,
Whitehead.

45:02.177 --> 45:05.615
So how did
Whitehead get the gun?

45:05.659 --> 45:08.140
Could you explain that to me?
'Cause from where I stand,

45:08.183 --> 45:10.708
I think your multimillion-
dollar settlement

45:10.751 --> 45:12.927
is disappearing.

45:12.971 --> 45:14.494
What does that mean?

45:14.537 --> 45:16.322
What does a nod mean?

45:16.365 --> 45:19.760
We skimmed guns from busts.

45:19.804 --> 45:21.501
You and Whitehead?

45:21.544 --> 45:23.633
Yeah.

45:23.677 --> 45:25.853
The weapons we seized
were popular on the street.

45:25.897 --> 45:27.420
They made the
perfect drop gun.

45:27.463 --> 45:29.291
We'd give 'em to officers
who asked for one.

45:29.335 --> 45:30.815
Why did Whitehead shoot you?

45:30.858 --> 45:33.208
My guess is, he thought
I was gonna turn on him.

45:33.252 --> 45:36.168
Just wait, wait.

45:36.211 --> 45:37.952
We need to leave now.

45:37.996 --> 45:40.215
Why?Oh, God, you're right.

45:40.259 --> 45:42.435
Attorney-client
privilege.

45:42.478 --> 45:44.002
We can't be listening to this.

45:49.616 --> 45:52.053
Okay.

45:52.097 --> 45:54.752
Tell us everything.

45:54.795 --> 45:56.971
What happens to my lawsuit?

45:57.015 --> 45:58.973
If we're lucky,
and you tell the truth,

45:59.017 --> 46:02.281
the whole truth,

46:02.324 --> 46:04.457
maybe we can get a deal.

46:15.468 --> 46:18.166
The great society.

46:18.210 --> 46:21.256
I look out there and I see a
world that could have been.

46:21.300 --> 46:23.258
Diversity.
Cooperation.

46:23.302 --> 46:25.086
You did a lot
to foster that, sir.

46:25.130 --> 46:28.829
Feels like a dream.
So long ago.

46:28.873 --> 46:31.005
And maybe now this
is the nightmare.

46:31.049 --> 46:32.441
Oh, indeed it is.

46:32.485 --> 46:34.879
We made a discovery,
Mr. Waltzer.

46:34.922 --> 46:36.750
And we still think
that Chicago PD

46:36.794 --> 46:38.491
should pay $8.3 million.

46:38.534 --> 46:40.319
No.

46:42.582 --> 46:44.845
I didn't bring
my reading glasses.

46:44.889 --> 46:46.455
You don't wear
reading glasses.

46:46.499 --> 46:50.068
Those are all the
arrests Danny Whitehead made

46:50.111 --> 46:52.331
where he supposedly found guns
on the arrestees.

46:52.374 --> 46:54.507
Quite a few of them,
as you can see.

46:54.550 --> 46:55.943
Yeah, okay.

46:55.987 --> 46:57.292
And we've just
come across some information

46:57.336 --> 46:58.772
that those guns were planted
by Whitehead.

46:58.816 --> 47:01.557
Really?

47:01.601 --> 47:04.778
You've "just come across"

47:04.822 --> 47:06.432
Our client, Rashid Clarkson,

47:06.475 --> 47:08.086
supplied Whitehead
those drop guns.

47:08.129 --> 47:09.652
We think
there are 20 or 30

47:09.696 --> 47:12.351
felons in prison because
of Whitehead's testimony

47:12.394 --> 47:13.787
that they had
guns on them.

47:13.831 --> 47:15.049
And this came from your client?

47:16.485 --> 47:18.313
Yeah.

47:18.357 --> 47:20.315
And due to attorney-client
privilege, you can't use it?

47:20.359 --> 47:22.056
Unless he allows us to.

47:22.100 --> 47:24.145
♪

47:27.845 --> 47:29.672
So this is no longer
about the law.

47:29.716 --> 47:31.936
This is a,
this is a game of poker?

47:31.979 --> 47:33.502
If you wish,

47:33.546 --> 47:36.070
but my guess is that Chicago PD
would rather pay up

47:36.114 --> 47:39.639
instead of having
30 prosecutions reopened.

47:39.682 --> 47:41.989
And here we are, four idealists

47:42.033 --> 47:44.774
casting lots
over Jesus' garments.

47:44.818 --> 47:46.559
If you wish.

47:48.604 --> 47:50.737
I'll talk to my client.

47:53.871 --> 47:56.264
And meanwhile,
you can all go fuck yourselves.

47:59.702 --> 48:02.575
Obviously, we feel awful.

48:02.618 --> 48:04.925
Because we believe in your case,

48:04.969 --> 48:06.840
but now we have
a conflict of interest.

48:06.884 --> 48:09.756
You can't even tell me
what the conflict is?

48:09.799 --> 48:11.149
Well, I'm afraid even
explaining the conflict,

48:11.192 --> 48:12.890
I mean, that would
breach legal ethics.

48:12.933 --> 48:16.676
God, that
sounded lame. Uh...

48:16.719 --> 48:19.157
Craig, I'm sorry.

48:19.200 --> 48:20.985
We are so sorry.

48:21.028 --> 48:22.595
We will help you find
another lawyer.

48:22.638 --> 48:24.640
Sure.

48:26.294 --> 48:27.513
Thanks.

48:29.994 --> 48:31.952
We can file a
post-conviction petition

48:31.996 --> 48:33.258
based on
actual innocence.

48:33.301 --> 48:35.477
We can't, but
someone else can.

48:35.521 --> 48:36.696
Like who?

48:36.739 --> 48:38.916
Someone who doesn't
work at our firm.

48:38.959 --> 48:41.570
Like a public defender
with no time and no resources?

48:41.614 --> 48:43.529
We have no options.

48:43.572 --> 48:45.487
This is stupid. This is...

48:45.531 --> 48:47.968
Let's go.

48:56.150 --> 48:58.936
We couldn't have gotten this settlement without Marissa

48:58.979 --> 49:00.459
kicking ass.

49:02.026 --> 49:03.853
Hear, hear!
Hear, hear!

49:03.897 --> 49:04.942
Okay, okay.

49:04.985 --> 49:06.769
Thank you,
but I had a lot of help.

49:06.813 --> 49:08.336
And Jay, too.

49:20.174 --> 49:21.784
♪ Tonight is the night

49:28.661 --> 49:31.620
♪ The night of your life

49:31.664 --> 49:33.100
♪ The night of your life...

49:33.144 --> 49:34.406
Good job, Jay.

49:34.449 --> 49:37.626
Adrian, can I
talk to you?

49:37.670 --> 49:40.586
Oh. I'm in trouble.

49:40.629 --> 49:42.327
Somebody call
my lawyer.

49:42.370 --> 49:45.547
And I'll tell
you what.

49:45.591 --> 49:47.593
Don't drink up all my liquor.

49:47.636 --> 49:49.987
Too late.

50:00.910 --> 50:04.958
$8.3 million.

50:05.002 --> 50:08.875
We haven't had that big
a payday in a year.

50:08.918 --> 50:12.096
You accepted
the gag rule.

50:12.139 --> 50:15.838
I... What

50:15.882 --> 50:18.058
Chicago PD's gag rule.

50:18.102 --> 50:22.106
You agreed to it.
No.

50:22.149 --> 50:25.500
Attorney-client privilege.
Rashid is our client.

50:25.544 --> 50:26.936
That's our gag rule.

50:28.982 --> 50:31.985
What's the matter, Jay?

50:32.029 --> 50:34.553
My friend Craig has been
rotting away in prison

50:34.596 --> 50:37.947
because of a bullshit gun charge
Whitehead slapped on him.

50:37.991 --> 50:40.776
Okay.This settlement

50:40.820 --> 50:42.691
fucked him over.

50:42.735 --> 50:44.824
What are you talking about?

50:44.867 --> 50:47.174
We needed Rashid's statement
about the planted gun.

50:47.218 --> 50:48.436
Yeah, but we can't use that

50:48.480 --> 50:49.698
without getting
our client's permission.

50:49.742 --> 50:51.352
Then why don't we try to get it?

50:51.396 --> 50:52.832
Because your friend's
not my client, Jay.

50:52.875 --> 50:55.313
Rashid is, and we have a duty

50:55.356 --> 50:57.271
to represent and protect him
from risk.

50:57.315 --> 50:58.751
Even if he's a dirty cop?

50:58.794 --> 51:02.102
Rashid's morality
wasn't on trial here.

51:02.146 --> 51:05.236
This case was about an unarmed
black undercover cop

51:05.279 --> 51:07.238
shot by a white cop...

51:07.281 --> 51:08.804
No, this case was about
two crooked cops

51:08.848 --> 51:10.458
who turned on each other.

51:10.502 --> 51:13.331
And one of them got rich and the
other one walked away scot-free.

51:13.374 --> 51:15.072
And people like Craig
rot in prison.

51:17.987 --> 51:20.294
Jay, if your friend
is innocent,

51:20.338 --> 51:22.949
we can pick that up without
using Rashid's statement.

51:22.992 --> 51:24.907
Now, it might take
a little bit longer

51:24.951 --> 51:26.561
to get him out,
but, hey...

51:26.605 --> 51:29.042
"But, hey," we can let Craig sit
in prison so you can get rich.

51:29.086 --> 51:31.784
You know how things work
in these cases.

51:31.827 --> 51:33.742
As your boss,
I got to tell you,

51:33.786 --> 51:36.267
you're being childish
and you're being unprofessional.

51:36.310 --> 51:39.966
I'm not being unprofessional.
I'm telling the truth.

51:40.009 --> 51:43.361
Jay, I am sorry things
didn't work out for your friend.

51:43.404 --> 51:45.580
But what makes you think
that you have the right

51:45.624 --> 51:48.322
to come up in my firm
acting like this?

51:48.366 --> 51:50.194
Because it's our firm, too!

51:50.237 --> 51:52.109
The people
who work here,

51:52.152 --> 51:53.980
who sacrifice their time,
who put in the hours,

51:54.023 --> 51:56.678
who pour their heart out so that
you can hustle some slick game.

51:56.722 --> 51:58.811
Did you say "hustle" So I'm a hustler now?

51:58.854 --> 52:00.247
If the shoe fits.
Hey.

52:00.291 --> 52:02.858
Hey. If I'm a hustler, you are,
you are an ignorant...

52:02.902 --> 52:04.164
What?

52:04.208 --> 52:05.992
I'm an ignorant what?

52:06.035 --> 52:08.995
Man, get the fuck
out of my office

52:09.038 --> 52:10.997
before I put my
foot up your ass.

52:11.040 --> 52:13.521
No, you're not
even worth it.

52:13.565 --> 52:16.176
I quit.

